item.title: Tensorflow and Gsteam
item.description: TensorFlow inference with GStreamer GStreamer GStreamer is a framework for creating streaming media applications and plugins: Application programmers can build media pipeline easily without writing a single line of code using its extensive set of plugins. Plugin programmers can use its clean and simple API to create self-contained plugins. It also provides a set of extensible base classes that can be use by object inheritance. Check more about GStreamer on its official documentation
